lead_paragraph: Two views of Jeff Feagles, who retired on Friday after 22 seasons:
snippet: If coaches continue to increase their fourth-down attempts in the middle part of the field, there will be a higher premium on booming punts, and less of a need for coffin-corner punting. Or so it would seem.

headline.main: Feagles's Style Going Out of Style?
